From 95c89ad60076d77be6632349d8ac71a397ff4003 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dave Airlie <airlied@redhat.com>
Date: Tue, 30 Mar 2010 05:34:16 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 4/9] drm/kms/fb: provide a 1024x768 fbcon if no outputs found.

commit 19b4b44503ccdf834062d68e022dc1e2721695a5 upstream

If we get no outputs setup provide a 1024x768 fbcon, with
this + radeon hotplug stuff I can plug a monitor in after startup
and get to see stuff.

Last thing is to add some sort of timer for non-hpd outputs like
VGA etc.

Signed-off-by: Dave Airlie <airlied@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Yue Tao <Yue.Tao@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/drm_fb_helper.c |    4 +++-
 1 files changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_fb_helper.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_fb_helper.c
index d63884e..7218559 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_fb_helper.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/drm_fb_helper.c
@@ -897,7 +897,9 @@ int drm_fb_helper_single_fb_probe(struct drm_fb_helper *fb_helper,
 	if (crtc_count == 0 || sizes.fb_width == -1 || sizes.fb_height == -1) {
 		/* hmm everyone went away - assume VGA cable just fell out
 		   and will come back later. */
-		return 0;
+		DRM_ERROR("Cannot find any crtc or sizes - going 1024x768\n");
+		sizes.fb_width = sizes.surface_width = 1024;
+		sizes.fb_height = sizes.surface_height = 768;
 	}
 
 	/* push down into drivers */
